The '''Sulawesi leaf warbler''' ('''''Phylloscopus nesophilus''''') is a species of [[Old World warbler]] in the family [[Phylloscopidae]]. It is found only in [[Sulawesi Island]], [[Indonesia]]. The Sulawesi leaf warbler (''P. nesophilus'') was formerly considered conspecific with the [[Lompobattang leaf warbler]] and both were grouped under the name ''P. sarasinorum'', but more recent analyses indicate that it is a distinct species.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Species Updates – IOC World Bird List|url=https://www.worldbirdnames.org/new/updates/species-updates/|access-date=2021-05-28|language=en-US}}</ref>

